A governorship aspirant on the platform of the All Progress Congress APC, Otunba Demola Popoola has denied the allegation in a viral video that he brought some thugs to disrupt the APC primary election. In a statement in Ado Ekiti, Otunba Popoola described the allegation as a script by desperate politicians who intend to dent his hard-earned image by trying to bring out issues from nothing. Ekiti State Police Command had apprehended some suspects on Wednesday and questioned them. The suspects in their statements said they came to Ekiti State to provide security for Otunba Popoola during his tour and they were about to set out, but some personalities misconstrued the statement and alleged that Popoola brought thugs. The statement by Popoola reads “Please note these facts from the respondents to the questions in the viral video “First, according to the confession, it was revealed that the people arrested were not thugs, hooligans or hired assassins but members of the Odua People’s Congress, OPC “Secondly, there have been several threats to life, calls from other contenders to all Otunba’Demola Popoola ODEP’s Ward Coordinators which had earlier been petitioned and submitted to the DSS and AIG “Third, according to the confession from the members of Odua People’s Congress, they were not invited to disrupt the APC Primary Election but to protect and defend Otunba’ Demola Popoola and his team from being attacked during his Local Government Tour, which ended yesterday